      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROBIN CARGO (1) had the drop on the lead early on but could only manage third, beaten 5.5 lengths (20.23) at this track in a Grade 5 over 340m. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can go on with it. HARA'S ROCKY (2) is progressing well with another good run, placing by 2.25 lengths (20.08) in a Grade 5 at this track. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Expected to be in the finish again. KIANDO DIVA (8) has been in the money at her last two runs, most recently when third (20.03) in a Grade 5 over 340m at this track. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Can find the frame this time. JOHNNY DEXTER (3) looks a top-three hope after a break.",
